    <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">When You Need a Retaining Wall</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">A lot of Las Cruces properties sit on sloped or uneven ground — especially in the foothills, Picacho Hills, and areas along the Rio Grande corridor. Without something holding the soil in place, monsoon rains move dirt, undermine foundations, and wash out landscaping.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">David builds retaining walls that solve the structural problem and fit the property. Every wall starts with proper excavation, compacted base material, and drainage behind the wall so water pressure doesn't build up and push things apart. That's the part most homeowners never see — and the part that determines whether the wall lasts 5 years or 25.</p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Segmental Block Walls</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Interlocking concrete blocks for clean lines and consistent look. Available in multiple colors and textures to match your property.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Natural Stone Walls</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Stacked stone for a more organic feel. Works well in desert landscapes where you want the wall to blend with the surroundings.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Boulder Walls</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Large boulders placed with equipment for a rugged, natural-looking solution on steep slopes and larger grade changes.</p></div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Terraced Walls</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Multiple shorter walls that step down a slope — easier to build, better drainage, and creates planting pockets between tiers.</p></div>
